1
00:00:04,347 --> 00:00:09,807
The central conception of the Absolute, 
the Ultimate Reality, is Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa.

2
00:00:10,027 --> 00:00:12,248
[Who is Krishna? Who is the Girl with Krishna?]

3
00:00:12,528 --> 00:00:18,158
Prabhupād … The “Kṛṣṇa” book 
is so beautuful and …

4
00:00:19,654 --> 00:00:24,586
I remember that lady, artist, Devahuti.
She made that painting.

5
00:00:24,586 --> 00:00:28,118
Still a very beautiful painting—
”Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa”.

6
00:00:28,118 --> 00:00:29,498
And what’s Prabhupād saying
in the beginning? 
 

7
00:00:29,498 --> 00:00:30,761
It’s very simple, 
he says,

8
00:00:30,761 --> 00:00:33,172
“When people see a book like …”, 
I mean, just …

9
00:00:33,172 --> 00:00:37,752
He’s trying to really 
make it simple for people,

10
00:00:37,752 --> 00:00:41,637
so what’s he called the book? 
“Kṛṣṇa”.

11
00:00:43,297 --> 00:00:45,752
The ‘Kṛṣṇa’ book.

12
00:00:46,442 --> 00:00:48,519
And what does he say 
in the beginning?

13
00:00:48,519 --> 00:00:52,668
“When people see a book 
like, ‘Kṛṣṇa’,

14
00:00:52,668 --> 00:00:56,198
and with the cover,” he said, 
“they immediately ask,

15
00:00:56,198 --> 00:01:00,588
‘Who is Kṛṣṇa,
and who is the girl with Kṛṣṇa?’”

16
00:01:02,014 --> 00:01:07,274
If you can answer those two questions, 
you can understand the Supreme Reality.

17
00:01:07,622 --> 00:01:10,862
And … and any other type of reality.

18
00:01:10,862 --> 00:01:14,382
And then you can learn how 
to measure this reality against that one.

